> Make sure that your ground is really clean and good (like to a solid piece
> of metal, not the engine tin or something like that. Sounds to me like your
> engine is not grounded well and something trying to FIND ground. When you
> operate the lights, the ground is made more complete and the ignition is
> able to function without excessive amperage wicking through it to complete a
> circuit.
